def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    index = data.index

    if isinstance(index, MultiIndex):
        names = index.names or [None]  # If no names are provided, use [None]

        # Extract level numbers from the index
        clocs = [index._get_level_number(i) for i in clocs]

        dummy_index = MultiIndex(
            levels=index.levels,  # Use existing levels for the unstacked index
            codes=index.codes,  # Use existing codes for the unstacked index
            names=names,  # Use existing names for the unstacked index
            verify_integrity=False,
        )

        # Create a dummy DataFrame with the unstacked index
        dummy = data.copy()
        dummy.index = dummy_index

        # Perform unstacking
        unstacked = dummy.unstack(list(clocs), fill_value=fill_value)

        return unstacked

    else:
        # If not a MultiIndex, return the unaltered DataFrame
        return data
